POLOKWANE – With an extreme passion for decor and catering, the owner and founder of La Patrician Events, Maboshego Patricia Letebele from Flora Park, said her company should be the go-to for parties and events. The mother of one and sports fanatic founded La Patrician Events in 2020, when the economy suffered a huge blow as a result of the Covid-19 pandemic. Maboshego decided to come up with a solution to bridge the gap and also create job opportunities by doing what she is passionate about. “I want clients to save their time and ease their stress by coming to us for our services. Hiring decor and catering companies gives you one less thing to organise and gives you a chance to focus on other aspects of your event. Relax and let us treat you with the best service one can offer,” she told Review. She explained that the company’s name was inspired by by her second name ‘Patricia’, which is derived from the Latin word ‘patrician’ meaning ‘noble’. “It is of utmost importance to commit myself to showcasing high moral principle when rendering services to my clients,” she said. She said that her business has given her the opportunity to create casual work opportunities, depending on the size of the project.  Maboshego added she is usually assisted by her younger sisters Ntoso and Ramalau. La Patrician Events caters for glamourous weddings, parties, baby and bridal showers, events and equipment hire. They can be found on Instagram (@patrician_events) and Facebook (La_Patrician_Events).   A post shared by LA ‘PATRICIAN_EVENTS (@patrician_events) Contact Maboshego on 076 169 9852 or 071 251 2099. Alternatively, send an email to maboshegopatricialetebele@gmail.com or visit their website www.lapatriciaevents.co.za. 